---
import PostLayout from "../../layouts/PostLayout.astro";
import Separator from "../../components/Separator.tsx";
---

<PostLayout title="5 Essential Skills for Web Developers">
  <main class="dark:bg-neutral-900 h-full flex relative">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] xl:pl-28 pt-8 p-5 lg:mr-20">
      <a
        href="/"
        class="mb-20 flex items-center gap-2 text-neutral-950 dark:text-neutral-100"
      >
        <span>
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            fill="none"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            stroke="currentColor"
            class="size-5"
          >
            <path
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              d="M10.5 19.5 3 12m0 0 7.5-7.5M3 12h18"></path>
          </svg>
        </span>
        Back
      </a>
      <h2
        class="tracking-tight text-balance lg:text-4xl text-2xl font-medium dark:text-white text-neutral-900"
      >
        5 Essential Skills for Web Developers
      </h2>
      <p class="lg:text-sm text-base mt-2 text-neutral-500 font-normal">
        Written by: <span class="underline mx-2">Amangoua</span> | Mon Apr 01 2024
      </p>

      <Separator />

      <p class="lg:text-lg text-base text-neutral-500 lg:my-4 my-1 font-normal">
        Web development is a rapidly evolving field, and keeping up with the
        latest trends and technologies can be challenging. In this post, we'll
        explore five essential skills that every web developer should master,
        from front-end frameworks to server-side languages. Whether you're just
        starting out or looking to level up your skills, this guide has
        everything you need to know.
      </p>

      <img
        class="w-[700px] h-[350px] object-auto object-right-bottom rounded-md shadow-3xl my-10"
        src="/skills.jpg"
        alt="skills"
      />

      <h2
        class="tracking-tight dark:text-white text-neutral-900 text-balance lg:text-4xl text-2xl font-medium"
      >
        5 Essential Skills for Web Developers
      </h2>
      <p class="lg:text-lg text-base text-neutral-500 lg:my-4 my-1 font-normal">
        In the rapidly evolving field of web development, staying abreast of the
        latest trends and technologies is paramount. Whether you’re a budding
        developer or a seasoned pro, mastering a core set of skills is essential
        to navigating the digital landscape successfully. Here’s a look at five
        critical areas every web developer should focus on
      </p>

      <h3
        id="1"
        class="tracking-tight dark:text-white text-neutral-900 text-balance lg:text-2xl text-xl font-medium"
      >
        1. Proficiency in Front-End Technologies
      </h3>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-5">
        <li>
          <p
            class="lg:text-sm text-base text-neutral-500 lg:my-4 my-1 font-normal"
          >
            <span class="text-white">HTML/CSS</span> : The building blocks of the
            web. Understanding how to structure content and style it effectively
            is crucial.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p
            class="lg:text-sm text-base text-neutral-500 lg:my-4 my-1 font-normal"
          >
            <span class="text-white">HTML/CSS </span>: The building blocks of
            the web. Understanding how to structure content and style it
            effectively is crucial.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h3
        id="2"
        class="tracking-tight dark:text-white text-neutral-900 text-balance lg:text-2xl text-xl font-medium"
      >
        2. Back-End Development Skills
      </h3>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-5">
        <li>
          <p
            class="lg:text-sm text-base text-neutral-500 lg:my-4 my-1 font-normal"
          >
            <span class="text-white">Server-side Languages:</span> Proficiency in
            languages such as Node.js, Python, Ruby, or PHP is essential for building
            the logic behind web applications.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p
            class="lg:text-sm text-base text-neutral-500 lg:my-4 my-1 font-normal"
          >
            <span class="text-white">Databases </span>: Understanding how to
            work with databases, both SQL (e.g., MySQL, PostgreSQL) and NoSQL
            (e.g., MongoDB), is crucial for data management.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h3
        id="3"
        class="tracking-tight dark:text-white text-neutral-900 text-balance lg:text-2xl text-xl font-medium"
      >
        3. Version Control
      </h3>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-5">
        <li>
          <p
            class="lg:text-sm text-base text-neutral-500 lg:my-4 my-1 font-normal"
          >
            <span class="text-white">Git:</span> A version control system that allows
            you to track changes, revert to previous stages, and collaborate with
            others. It’s an industry standard for a reason.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div
      class="border-l border-neutral-700 p-20 hidden xl:block sticky top-0 h-full"
    >
      <ol class="list-decimal text-sm space-y-2 font-['AtiplaND']">
        <li>
          <a href="#1"> Proficiency in Front-End Technologies </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="#2"> Back-End Development Skills </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="#3"> Version Control </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="#1"> Understanding of UX/UI Design Principles </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="#1"> Continuous Learning and Adaptability </a>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </main>
</PostLayout>
